summary: SummaryHighlightsSustainable PackagingBobbi Brown Long-Wear Cream Eyeliner Stick features a fine-tip design for effortless eyeliner looks with waterproof, 24-hour wear.
details: DetailsBenefitsCreamy formula glides on with swipe-and-go easeLines for definition and smudges for softer eyeliner looksPigment-rich shades level up every look and play perfectly with Long-Wear Cream Shadow Stick24-hour non-creasing, non-flaking, non-smudging, color-true wear stays the day (and night)FeaturesFine-tip design makes sleek, defined looks effortlessCreamy, blendable, fan-favorite formula smudges softly for smokey eye looksBuilt-in sharpener keeps your look on pointItem 2621912How To UseFor a sleek line, apply in short strokes across lash line, starting at the outer half of eye and working inward.To create a winged eyeliner look, draw line slightly past outer corner, then swipe finger gently along bottom of line to extend into a sharp flick.For a softer eyeliner look, blend the top edge of the line with fingers or our Smokey Eyeliner Brush. reviews.headline: Very creamy yet too fragile
reviews.comments: It is nice creamy texture, yet too fragile to handle

reviews.headline: Too Dry and Hard to Work With
reviews.comments: This eyeliner felt chalky and didn't glide on smoothlyâ€”I had to go over the same spot multiple times just to get decent payoff. It might work for someone with more experience, but it wasn't beginner-friendly for me. I ended up returning it.

reviews.headline: Will buy this in all colors
reviews.comments: I have FINALLY found the perfect  eyeliner stick.  It's so easy.  I am 67 and really don't like the saggy eye skin and trying to make them look pretty.  Well - I found it and I'm not going back.  Ya'll need to give this a shot, you will not regret it.

reviews.headline: Not great for the price
reviews.comments: When I bought it the eyeliner was already broken and stuck in the cap. I didn't want to go back so kept it, as I was able to retrieve the tip. Fast forward the tip always breaks so easily even when sharpening with the built in sharpner. The color is pretty and glides nicely BUT it smears so easily. One wrong move and it was smeared all under my eye. I feel for the price the product should NOT be like this.

reviews.headline: Yes
reviews.comments: Soft goes on nice. Only problem is I haven't figured out how to sharpen it

reviews.headline: No
reviews.comments: Goes on easily but less than a week in and the whole "crayon" part broke off and I had never twisted up all the way up. Ok fine, I can still use it.  A few weeks later, the whole tip breaks off. Disappointing for the price.

reviews.headline: Its ok
reviews.comments: I expected better performance from this based on the price and reviews. I got brown and while the color is beautiful and it applies smoothly, it does not stay put. Smudged and smeared within hours. I took a chance on it since it was 50% off but would not repurchase at any price.

reviews.headline: Don't waste your money.
reviews.comments: When I first bought it I had to return it because the tip was broken and stuck in the cap. I received a new one, the color is beautiful but it is NOT long wear, it smears easily. Sure enough after a few uses the tip broke again.

reviews.headline: Long lasting and silky liner
reviews.comments: I've tried every eyeliner out there and very few last until I get to my destination, much less all day. This one is shockingly creamy and easy to apply with no tugging and no bleeding, either. And it lasts allllllll day. I got no free product to review. I just want everyone to know this is the real deal and worth every penny. I got it in Jungle, which could have been a harsh green but it's so soft and pretty. It is more like a dark khaki green but very pretty with my fair skin and blue eyes. I will certainly get this again.

reviews.headline: Does not last. Smudges.
reviews.comments: The eyeliner is very thick so you can't draw a thin line. The liner (I got both the black and brown) also does not last. I used it on my upper lash line and I had panda eyes in a few hours. I tried it many times and the eyeliner would disappear and bleed. So disappointed.

reviews.headline: Too soft and tip breaks off
reviews.comments: I liked it when it was first opened and it had a point but it turned out the pencil is so creamy soft it wears completely down after applying to just one lid. Between constant sharpening and the tip often breaking off when doing so this pencil will probably be gone in a couple weeks. Definitely not worth the top tier price.

reviews.headline: BB Liner Stick in Aubergine
reviews.comments: First off, I had read reviews about the liner sticks arriving broken; however, I decided to take a chance and purchase it anyway. When I opened it for the first time yesterday, the top part of the liner was broken and fell right out. I had to hold it in place and smush it together to get it to stick. It held up for the time being; disappointing nonetheless.  Other than that, the liner is creamy and glides on smoothly on the eyelid. It lasts all day and does not smudge. Just disappointed that it was broken when I opened it. Hence, one star was removed for that flaw. It may be a common complaint with this particular shade.

reviews.headline: Not crazy about the color
reviews.comments: I bought this because I wanted a dark Green. It goes on green but then it gets a funny brown color. It's kind of weird I'm not sure if I'm going to keep. Would not buy this color again. It goes on smooth so maybe I'll try a different color

reviews.headline: LOVE IT! Very smooth line!
reviews.comments: I'm a 66 yo fem with aging eyes, making it increasingly diffficult to get a smooth sleek line on my upper lid.  I had given up on liquid eye liner long ago, resorting to a fine angled brush and eye shadow to create the line.  During Ulta's 21 days of beauty I decided to try Bobbi Browns cream eyeliner stick-- all I can say is WOW!!! I'm back baby!!  Goes on so smooth and looks beautiful!  Makes my eyes look younger bc I can achieve the line I used to be able to get years ago.  Will DEF be buying this again!  Thank you Bobbi Brown!!

reviews.headline: High hopes
reviews.comments: I had high hopes for this eyeliner since it was super easy to apply but the product continued to smudge and flake off after just a few hours.  I often struggle with eyeliner transferring to my upper lids so this product was a no for me, just too creamy and smudgy for my liking.

reviews.headline: Perfect eyeliner
reviews.comments: Broke so easily before even trying it :( bir it was beautiful and one of the best eyeliner except for the durability!

reviews.headline: I love this eyeliner!
reviews.comments: This eye liner does on so smoothly and does Not smear! It is great for more mature skin. I have bought the colors rich chocolate and fog. Love this eyeliner!

reviews.headline: Must have
reviews.comments: I don't ever leave reviews. But this is by far the only eyeliner i have used that actually works. I habe combo skin and it stayed in place after a full 9hr work day. I've bought multiple colors of Urban Decay, Makeup by Mario, stila, charlotte Tillbury you name it. This is hands down the best eyeliner!!!

reviews.headline: Love BB
reviews.comments: I believe that Bobbi Brown make up is worth the price! I was introduced to the foundation first, and it was over for most other brands for me except RMS Beauty: I love their products as well. I ordered this in the panther and the dark chocolate color.  Product is very pigmented, it blends well with a smudging brush and it stays put! I will continue to buy this product and try more from her line in the future!

reviews.headline: I wanted an item Ulta was out of -
reviews.comments: The liner is nice and soft but not at all the color I wanted. I wish Ulta would fix its in stock position or offer free shipping

faceoff_positive.comments:
Bobbi Brown's Long-Wear Cream Liner Stick is a makeup essential that truly delivers. Its creamy texture glides effortlessly onto the eyelids, allowing for precise application with minimal effort. The intense pigmentation ensures a bold and defined look that lasts throughout the day without fading or smudging.

What sets this liner apart is its long-wear formula, which stays put for hours without requiring touch-ups. Whether facing a busy day at work or a night out on the town, you can trust this liner to maintain its flawless appearance from morning until night.

Furthermore, its convenient stick format makes it travel-friendly and easy to use on the go. With just a few swipes, you can achieve a professional-looking eyeliner that enhances your eyes and adds depth to your overall makeup look.

Gifted by bobbibrown. The range of shades available caters to various preferences and occasions, from classic black for a timeless look to more adventurous colors for those wanting to make a statement. Regardless of the shade chosen, you can expect rich color payoff and a smooth, even application every time.

In summary, Bobbi Brown's Long-Wear Cream Liner Stick is a reliable and versatile product that deserves a spot in any makeup collection. Its long-lasting formula, ease of use, and impressive color payoff make it a standout choice for achieving flawless eyeliner looks with minimal effort.
faceoff_positive.headline: Nice

faceoff_negative.comments: I received this Longwear Cream Liner Stick in the shade Aubergine complimentary from bobbibrown in exchange for a review. I love this shade of purple, it really makes my eyes pop. I use this liner for a quick pop of color for days when I feel lazy, and I have yet to use it as a base. I could see it being great as a base because it is very longlasting and doesn't smear on the rest of the lids (I do like to use it over an eyeshadow primer though but that's because I have very oily lids). It is not easy to get a precise liner with this stick so, to make it look sharper, you could go in with some concealer. I would say that, if you like more of a chunky/grungy liner, it would be good for that, which I don't mind. I did not succeed smoking it because, once it is applied, it doesn't not budge (which is also a pro as it is longlasting). I also had to trace the liner several times because it doesn't apply very evenly unfortunately. I have mixed feelings about this. I feel like it would be good if you want a small touch of purple but it doesn't give me the application I am looking for and it is not as creamy as I thought it would be.
faceoff_negative.headline: Longlasting but not very precise and opaque nor very creamy
